===Verb===
{{en-verb}}

# {{lb|en|transitive}} To give something colour.
#: {{syn|en|dye|paint|stain|shade|tinge|tint}}
#: {{ux|en|We could '''colour''' the walls red.}}
## {{lb|en|transitive}} To cause (a pipe, especially a [[meerschaum]]) to take on a brown or black colour, by smoking.
# {{lb|en|intransitive}} To apply colours to the areas within the boundaries of a line drawing using coloured markers or crayons.
#: {{syn|en|colour in}}
#: {{ux|en|My kindergartener loves to '''colour'''.}}
# {{lb|en|of a person or their face}} To become red through increased blood flow.
#:{{syn|en|blush}}
#: {{ux|en|Her face '''coloured''' as she realized her mistake.}}
# To affect without completely changing.
#: {{syn|en|affect|influence}}
#: {{ux|en|That interpretation certainly '''colours''' my perception of the book.}}
# {{lb|en|informal}} To attribute a quality to; to portray (as).
#: {{syn|en|call}}
#: {{ux|en|'''Colour''' me confused.}}
#: {{ux|en|They tried to '''colour''' the industrial unrest as a merely local matter.}}
# {{lb|en|mathematics|graph theory}} To [[assign]] colours to the [[vertex|vertices]] of a [[graph]] (''or'' the [[region]]s of a [[map]]) so that no two vertices connected by an [[edge]] (regions sharing a border) have the [[same]] colour.
#: {{ux|en|Can this graph be 2-'''coloured'''?}}
#: {{ux|en|You can '''colour''' any map with four colours.}}

